# Core toolchain presence. Add project-specific tools via "extra_tools" in
# whereami.config.json or drop your own .cap in <project>/.whereami/probes.d/.

Capability vcs.git
  Description Local git operations
  Probe cmd git
  Remediation Install git, or drive GitHub through the GitHub MCP server / gh api from a capable environment.
  Risk low
  Environments local cloud ci

Capability vcs.gh
  Description GitHub CLI (repos, PRs, API)
  Probe cmd gh
  Remediation Install the gh CLI and run gh auth login, or use the GitHub MCP server.
  Risk low
  Environments local ci

Capability runtime.node
  Description Node.js runtime for JS/TS builds
  Probe cmd node
  Remediation Install Node.js (Claude Code ships as a native binary, so node is not guaranteed on the host).
  Risk low
  Environments local cloud ci

Capability runtime.python
  Description Python runtime
  Probe cmd python3 python
  Remediation Install Python 3.
  Risk low
  Environments local cloud ci

Capability media.ffmpeg
  Description Audio/video encode, transcode, render
  Probe cmd ffmpeg
  Remediation Install ffmpeg, or hand off media rendering to an environment that has it.
  Risk low
  Environments local

Capability docs.pdf-tools
  Description PDF rasterize/inspect (poppler)
  Probe cmd pdftoppm pdftotext
  Remediation Install poppler-utils, or ask the operator to upload rendered page images.
  Risk low
  Environments local

Capability infra.docker
  Description Container builds and runs
  Probe cmd docker podman
  Remediation Install Docker or Podman, or delegate container work to CI.
  Risk low
  Environments local ci
